Apparently, the problem was with my nginx config. Here's the working conf, for anyone who runs into a similar issue:
```
location /sync-server/ {
		proxy_pass   http://127.0.0.1:9091/;
		proxy_set_header Host $host;
						
		proxy_http_version 1.1;
                proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
                proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
}
		
location /socket.io {
		proxy_pass   http://127.0.0.1:9091/socket.io;
		proxy_set_header Host $host;
			
		proxy_http_version 1.1;
                proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
                proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
}
```

sync-server is used for io.connect, but socket.io is used in the path option, because otherwise it didn't work, for some reason.

Here is my solution:
I redefined a custom OpenAPIRenderer (subclassing the default one) in order to add the "scheme" field.  With this, my https request are properly processed.
It would be nice to have the possibility to make such customization from the module SETTINGS directly though. 

class OpenAPIRenderer(renderers.OpenAPIRenderer):
    def get_customizations(self):
        data = super(OpenAPIRenderer, self).get_customizations()
        data["schemes"] = ["https", "http"]
        return data


class SwaggerSchemaView(APIView):
    permission_classes = [permissions.IsAuthenticated]
    renderer_classes = [
        OpenAPIRenderer,
        renderers.SwaggerUIRenderer
    ]

    def get(self, request):
        generator = SchemaGenerator()
        schema = generator.get_schema(request=request)
        return Response(schema)

