`Function` might not be the best tool for the job though. It is really meant to transform an input value. If you don't need a value to deserialize, `Constant` is the right tool, but it does not currently support a callable value argument. The cleanest solution is probably to define a custom field.

https://marshmallow.readthedocs.io/en/2.x-line/custom_fields.html#custom-fields

```py
from marshmallow import fields

class DynamicConstant(fields.Constant):
    def _serialize(self, value, attr, obj):
        return self.constant()

    def _deserialize(self, value, attr, obj):
        return self.constant()
```
